    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>I</abbr><ex>ovi</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>O</abbr><ex>ptimo</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>aximo</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>ala I <expan><abbr>Can</abbr><ex>na</ex></expan><lb break="no" n="3"/>nefatium <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Aurelius <lb n="5"/>Dion<supplied reason="lost">ys</supplied>i<supplied reason="lost">us</supplied> <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Oberer Teil eines Altars. Z. 2: AL-Ligatur; Z. 3: NE-, TI-Ligaturen; Z. 4: AV-Ligatur. In Z. 6 dürfte der Rang (etwa [praef(ectus)]) des Dedikanten gestanden haben. Hošek datiert, wohl wegen des Gentilizes, auf nach 212. (B): Hošek: Z. 2/3: Can/nenafatium; Lőrincz: Z. 5: Diony[s]i[us]; Schmidtová - Jezná - Kozubová: Z. 5: Dion(ysius).</p>
            </div>
